main event: An observation was made on 11-12 Jan 51 from Lexington, KY to Atlanta, GA of a high-speed, flashing object evaluated as a meteor by local astronomers.
interesting points: The sighting was recorded on a Project 10073 record card, indicating official documentation of the event.
The object was described as moving at a high rate of speed, emitting shocks, and flying at an altitude of 1000+.
Local astronomers evaluated the object as a meteor, providing a possible prosaic explanation for the sighting.
The observation lasted for a few seconds, suggesting a brief but significant event.
Photographs were taken as part of the report, indicating potential visual evidence of the sighting.
witnesses: not mentioned in the provided report
